# Browser Automation Test Plan - User Payment Flow

## Context
The user wants to automate browser testing to simulate a complete user journey:
1. Sign up as a new user
2. Sign in with credentials  
3. Navigate to payment methods page
4. Add a payment method
5. Verify the payment method was added
6. Make a payment using the selected payment method

## Current Status
✅ **Already Implemented**: The repository already contains a comprehensive end-to-end test that covers all 6 steps exactly as requested!

### Existing Test File
- **Location**: `e2e-tests/tests/complete-user-flow.spec.ts`
- **Test Name**: "should complete full user journey: signup → signin → payment methods → add card → pay"
- **Framework**: Playwright
- **Coverage**: All 6 steps plus bonus dashboard verification

## Discovery

### Existing Implementation Details

**Step 1 - Signup**: Generates unique test user (test-{timestamp}@example.com), fills registration form (name, email, password, country, currency), submits and verifies dashboard redirect. Screenshot: 01-signup-success.png

**Step 2 - Signin**: Logs out, navigates to login, enters credentials, verifies dashboard redirect. Screenshot: 02-signin-success.png

**Step 3 - Navigate to Payment Methods**: Goes to /payment-methods, verifies page loaded. Screenshot: 03-payment-methods-page.png

**Step 4 - Add Payment Method**: Clicks "Add Payment Method", fills Stripe Elements iframe with test card 4242424242424242, expiry 12/30, CVC 123, ZIP 12345. Saves and waits for success. Screenshot: 04-payment-method-added.png

**Step 5 - Verify Added Payment Method**: Reloads page, verifies Visa brand, last 4 digits (•••• 4242), expiry (12/30), and "Default" label visible. Screenshot: 05-payment-method-visible.png

**Step 6 - Pay Using Selected Method**: Navigates to /payments/new, verifies payment method pre-selected, enters amount $99.99 and description, submits payment, verifies success message. Screenshot: 06-payment-success.png

**Bonus**: Dashboard verification - confirms transaction appears with amount, description, and "Completed" status. Screenshot: 07-dashboard-verification.png

